          "The series 1, 3, 6, 10, 15, 21 is a sequence of triangular \
numbers. Triangular numbers are the sums of the natural numbers up to a \
certain point. Specifically, the nth triangular number is the sum of the \
first n natural numbers.\n\nHere's how the sequence is generated:\n\n1. The \
1st triangular number is \\( 1 = 1 \\).\n2. The 2nd triangular number is \\( \
1 + 2 = 3 \\).\n3. The 3rd triangular number is \\( 1 + 2 + 3 = 6 \\).\n4. \
The 4th triangular number is \\( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 = 10 \\).\n5. The 5th \
triangular number is \\( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 = 15 \\).\n6. The 6th triangular \
number is \\( 1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6 = 21 \\).\n\nThe general formula for the \
nth triangular number is given by:\n\n\\[ T_n = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2} \\]\n\nThis \
formula represents the sum of the first n natural numbers, and applying it to \
each n in the sequence confirms the numbers given.\n\nFinal Answer: The \
series consists of triangular numbers; each term is the sum of the first n \
natural numbers, given by \\( T_n = \\frac{n(n+1)}{2} \\).", {7, 6}]], 
