multiplying the previous number by an incrementing integer starting from 2:\n\
\n- \\( 1 \\times 2 = 2 \\)\n- \\( 2 \\times 3 = 6 \\)\n- \\( 6 \\times 4 = \
24 \\)\n- \\( 24 \\times 5 = 120 \\)\n\nThis series follows the pattern of \
factorials:\n\n- The \\( n \\)-th term is \\( n! \\).\n\nTherefore, the \
pattern is that each term is the factorial of its position in the sequence:\n\
\n- \\( 1! = 1 \\)\n- \\( 2! = 2 \\)\n- \\( 3! = 6 \\)\n- \\( 4! = 24 \\)\n- \
\\( 5! = 120 \\)\n\nFinal Answer: The pattern is that each term is the \
factorial of its position in the sequence: \\( n! \\)."}}, 
