number:\\n\\n- 1 is the first term.\\n- 2 is obtained by multiplying 1 by 2 \
(1 * 2 = 2).\\n- 6 is obtained by multiplying 2 by 3 (2 * 3 = 6).\\n- 24 is \
obtained by multiplying 6 by 4 (6 * 4 = 24).\\n- 120 is obtained by \
multiplying 24 by 5 (24 * 5 = 120).\\n\\nWe can see that each term is the \
product of the previous term and a sequentially increasing integer. \
Specifically, the nth term is given by the product of the first n natural \
numbers, which means each term is a factorial:\\n\\n- 1 = 1!\\n- 2 = 2!\\n- 6 \
= 3!\\n- 24 = 4!\\n- 120 = 5!\\n\\nThus, the pattern is that each term is the \
factorial of its position in the sequence.\\n\\nFinal Answer: The pattern is \
factorials; the nth term is n!.\""}}, 
