inscribed in a semicircle with a given radius:\n\n```python\nimport math\n\n\
def largest_triangle_area(radius):\n    # The largest triangle inscribed in a \
semicircle is a right triangle\n    # with its base equal to the diameter of \
the semicircle and its height equal to the radius.\n    \n    # Base of the \
triangle (diameter of the semicircle)\n    base = 2 * radius\n    # Height of \
the triangle (radius of the semicircle)\n    height = radius\n    \n    # \
