\\( r_1 \\) and \\( r_2 \\) are reciprocal if \\( r_1 \\times r_2 = 1 \\). \
From Vieta's formulas, we know that \\( r_1 \\times r_2 = \\frac{c}{a} \\). \
Therefore, the roots are reciprocal if:\n\n\\[\n\\frac{c}{a} = 1 \\quad \
\\text{or equivalently} \\quad c = a\n\\]\n\nHere's a Python function to \
check this condition:\n\n```python\ndef are_roots_reciprocal(a, b, c):\n    # \
Check if the coefficients are valid for a quadratic equation\n    if a == 0:\n\
        raise ValueError(\"Coefficient 'a' must be non-zero for a quadratic \
equation.\")\n    \n    # Check if c equals a\n    return c == a\n\n# Example \
