              "\"To remove similar rows from a given tuple matrix, you can \
create a function that utilizes a set to track unique rows. Here's how to \
implement this in Python:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
remove_similar_rows(matrix):\\n    # Use a set to store unique rows\\n    \
unique_rows = set()\\n    \\n    # Create a list to store the result\\n    \
result = []\\n    \\n    for row in matrix:\\n        # Convert the row to a \
