              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Here\[CloseCurlyQuote]s a Python function that finds the \
greatest common divisor (gcd) of two integers using recursion:\\n\\n```python\
\\ndef gcd(a, b):\\n    # Base case: if b is 0, return a\\n    if b == 0:\\n  \
      return a\\n    # Recursive case: call gcd with b and the remainder of a \
divided by b\\n    return gcd(b, a % b)\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nresult = \
gcd(48, 18)\\nprint(result)  # Output: 6\\n```\\n\\nThis function uses the \
Euclidean algorithm, where the gcd of two numbers a and b is computed \
recursively by replacing the larger number with the remainder of the division \
of a by b until one of the numbers becomes zero.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
