= [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6]\\neven_count = \
count_even_elements(my_list)\\nprint(even_count)  # Output: 3\\n```\\n\\nIn \
this code:\\n1. `filter` applies the lambda function to each element in the \
list `lst`.\\n2. The lambda function checks if an element is even (`x % 2 == \
0`).\\n3. `list(filter(...))` converts the filtered result into a list.\\n4. \
`len(...)` counts the number of elements in that list, giving the number of \
even elements.\""}}, 
