              StyleBox["\"Prompt:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Write a python function to count the number of distinct \
power of prime factor of given number.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To count the number of distinct powers of prime factors of a \
given number, you can follow these steps:\\n\\n1. Factorize the given number \
into its prime factors.\\n2. Determine the power of each prime factor.\\n3. \
Count the number of distinct powers.\\n\\nHere's a Python function to achieve \
this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef count_distinct_prime_powers(n):\\n    def \
prime_factors(n):\\n        i = 2\\n        factors = {}\\n        while i * \
i <= n:\\n            while (n % i) == 0:\\n                if i in \
factors:\\n                    factors[i] += 1\\n                else:\\n     \
               factors[i] = 1\\n                n //= i\\n            i += \
1\\n        if n > 1:\\n            factors[n] = 1\\n        return \
factors\\n    \\n    factors = prime_factors(n)\\n    distinct_powers = \
set(factors.values())\\n    \\n    return len(distinct_powers)\\n\\n# Example \
usage\\nnumber = 180\\nresult = count_distinct_prime_powers(number)\\nprint(f\
\\\"The number of distinct powers of prime factors of {number} is {result}.\\\
\")\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- The `prime_factors` function factorizes a \
number into its prime factors and keeps track of the power (exponent) of each \
prime factor in a dictionary.\\n- We then extract the values (powers) from \
this dictionary and store them in a set to ensure uniqueness.\\n- The length \
of this set gives the count of distinct powers of prime factors.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
