standard_deviation = variance ** 0.5\\n    \\n    return \
standard_deviation\\n\\n# Example usage:\\ndata = [10, 20, 30, 40, \
50]\\nstd_dev = calculate_standard_deviation(data)\\nprint(\\\"Standard \
Deviation:\\\", std_dev)\\n```\\n\\nThis function calculates the standard \
deviation for a list of numbers. Note that it calculates the population \
standard deviation. If you need the sample standard deviation (where you \
divide by `n-1` instead of `n`), you can adjust the variance calculation by \
dividing by `(len(data) - 1)` instead of `len(data)`.\""}}, 
