              StyleBox["\"Prompt:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Write a function to filter the height and width of students \
which are stored in a dictionary.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To filter the height and width of students stored in a \
dictionary, you can write a function that receives the dictionary and the \
filter criteria, and returns a new dictionary with only the students that \
meet the criteria. Here's a basic example in Python:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
filter_students(students, min_height=None, max_height=None, min_width=None, \
max_width=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Filter students based on height and \
width.\\n\\n    :param students: Dictionary with student names as keys and a \
dictionary with 'height' and 'width' as values.\\n    :param min_height: \
Minimum height to filter students.\\n    :param max_height: Maximum height to \
filter students.\\n    :param min_width: Minimum width to filter students.\\n \
   :param max_width: Maximum width to filter students.\\n    :return: A \
dictionary with filtered students.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    filtered_students \
= {}\\n    \\n    for student, measurements in students.items():\\n        \
height = measurements.get('height')\\n        width = \
measurements.get('width')\\n        \\n        if (min_height is not None and \
height < min_height) or \\\\\\n           (max_height is not None and height \
> max_height) or \\\\\\n           (min_width is not None and width < \
min_width) or \\\\\\n           (max_width is not None and width > \
max_width):\\n            continue\\n        \\n        \
filtered_students[student] = measurements\\n\\n    return \
filtered_students\\n\\n# Example usage\\nstudents = {\\n    'Alice': \
{'height': 150, 'width': 50},\\n    'Bob': {'height': 160, 'width': 55},\\n   \
 'Charlie': {'height': 155, 'width': 60}\\n}\\n\\nresult = \
filter_students(students, min_height=155, max_width=55)\\nprint(result)\\n```\
\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- The function `filter_students` takes a dictionary \
`students` and optional filter criteria for height and width.\\n- It iterates \
over each student in the dictionary.\\n- For each student, it checks if their \
height and width fall outside the specified filter criteria.\\n- If a student \
does not meet the criteria, they are skipped.\\n- If they meet the criteria, \
