 \n        if (min_height is not None and height < min_height) or \\\n        \
   (max_height is not None and height > max_height) or \\\n           \
(min_width is not None and width < min_width) or \\\n           (max_width is \
not None and width > max_width):\n            continue\n        \n        \
filtered_students[student] = measurements\n\n    return filtered_students\n\n\
# Example usage\nstudents = {\n    'Alice': {'height': 150, 'width': 50},\n   \
 'Bob': {'height': 160, 'width': 55},\n    'Charlie': {'height': 155, \
'width': 60}\n}\n\nresult = filter_students(students, min_height=155, \
max_width=55)\nprint(result)\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n- The function \
`filter_students` takes a dictionary `students` and optional filter criteria \
for height and width.\n- It iterates over each student in the dictionary.\n- \
