**`str.maketrans`**: This method creates a translation table, mapping each \
character in the first string to the corresponding character in the second \
string. Here, every space, comma, or dot is mapped to a colon.\\n- \
**`str.translate`**: This method applies the translation table to the input \
string, replacing each specified character with a colon.\\n\\nYou can use \
