              "\"Write a function to locate the left insertion point for a \
specified value in sorted order.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To locate the left insertion point for a specified value in \
a sorted list, you can use a binary search algorithm. This task is often \
referred to as finding the \\\"lower bound\\\" of a value in a sorted list. \
Here's a Python function that accomplishes this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
find_left_insertion_point(sorted_list, value):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Finds \
the left insertion point for a specified value in a sorted list.\\n    \\n    \
Parameters:\\n    - sorted_list: A list of elements sorted in non-decreasing \
order.\\n    - value: The value to insert.\\n    \\n    Returns:\\n    - The \
index at which the value should be inserted to maintain sorted order.\\n    \
\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    left, right = 0, len(sorted_list)\\n    \\n    while left \
< right:\\n        mid = (left + right) // 2\\n        if sorted_list[mid] < \
value:\\n            left = mid + 1\\n        else:\\n            right = mid\
\\n    \\n    return left\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nsorted_list = [1, 2, 4, 4, \
5, 6]\\nvalue = 4\\nindex = find_left_insertion_point(sorted_list, \
value)\\nprint(index)  # Output will be 2\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- The \
function uses a binary search approach to efficiently find the left insertion \
point.\\n- `left` and `right` are initialized to the start and the end of the \
list, respectively.\\n- The loop continues until `left` is no longer less \
than `right`.\\n- In each iteration, `mid` is calculated as the middle point \
between `left` and `right`.\\n- If the value at `mid` is less than the \
specified value, `left` is updated to `mid + 1`, moving the search to the \
right half.\\n- Otherwise, `right` is updated to `mid`, narrowing the search \
to the left half.\\n- When the loop exits, `left` is the index where the \
specified value can be inserted to maintain sorted order.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
             "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}], "Grid"], 
          ImageSize -> {400, Automatic}]], Annotation[#, 
         Pane[
          Grid[{{
