              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To check if a given string starts with a vowel using regular \
expressions in Python, you can use the `re` module. Here's a function that \
accomplishes this:\\n\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef \
starts_with_vowel(s):\\n    # Define a regex pattern that matches any string \
