              "\"To calculate the area of a tetrahedron, you need the \
coordinates of its four vertices. The area of a tetrahedron can be broken \
down into the sum of the areas of its four triangular faces.\\n\\nHere's a \
Python function that calculates the area of a tetrahedron given the \
coordinates of its vertices:\\n\\n```python\\nimport numpy as np\\n\\ndef \
area_of_triangle(v1, v2, v3):\\n    # Calculate the area of a triangle using \
the cross product\\n    side1 = np.array(v2) - np.array(v1)\\n    side2 = \
np.array(v3) - np.array(v1)\\n    cross_product = np.cross(side1, side2)\\n   \
 area = np.linalg.norm(cross_product) / 2\\n    return area\\n\\ndef \
area_of_tetrahedron(v1, v2, v3, v4):\\n    # Calculate the area of each of \
the four faces\\n    face1 = area_of_triangle(v1, v2, v3)\\n    face2 = \
area_of_triangle(v1, v2, v4)\\n    face3 = area_of_triangle(v1, v3, v4)\\n    \
face4 = area_of_triangle(v2, v3, v4)\\n    \\n    # Sum of the areas of the \
four triangular faces\\n    total_area = face1 + face2 + face3 + face4\\n    \
return total_area\\n\\n# Example usage\\nv1 = [0, 0, 0]\\nv2 = [1, 0, 0]\\nv3 \
= [0, 1, 0]\\nv4 = [0, 0, 1]\\n\\ntotal_area = area_of_tetrahedron(v1, v2, \
v3, v4)\\nprint(\\\"Area of the tetrahedron:\\\", total_area)\\n```\\n\\n### \
Explanation\\n1. **`area_of_triangle(v1, v2, v3)`**: This helper function \
calculates the area of a triangle given its three vertices using the cross \
product to find the area of the parallelogram and then dividing by 2.\\n\\n2. \
**`area_of_tetrahedron(v1, v2, v3, v4)`**: This function calculates the total \
surface area of the tetrahedron by summing the areas of its four triangular \
faces.\\n\\nThis approach assumes you have the coordinates of the vertices of \
the tetrahedron. It uses `numpy` for vector operations to simplify the \
calculations.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
