              "\"Write a function to find the longest common subsequence for \
the given three string sequence.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find the longest common subsequence (LCS) among three \
strings, you can use dynamic programming. Here is a Python function to \
achieve this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef longest_common_subsequence(s1, s2, s3):\\n \
   # Get the lengths of the strings\\n    len1, len2, len3 = len(s1), \
len(s2), len(s3)\\n    \\n    # Create a 3D DP array to store lengths of \
LCS\\n    dp = [[[0] * (len3 + 1) for _ in range(len2 + 1)] for __ in \
range(len1 + 1)]\\n    \\n    # Build the dp array\\n    for i in range(1, \
len1 + 1):\\n        for j in range(1, len2 + 1):\\n            for k in \
range(1, len3 + 1):\\n                if s1[i - 1] == s2[j - 1] == s3[k - 1]:\
\\n                    dp[i][j][k] = dp[i - 1][j - 1][k - 1] + 1\\n           \
     else:\\n                    dp[i][j][k] = max(dp[i - 1][j][k], dp[i][j - \
1][k], dp[i][j][k - 1])\\n    \\n    # The length of LCS will be in \
dp[len1][len2][len3]\\n    return dp[len1][len2][len3]\\n\\n# Example \
usage\\ns1 = \\\"abc\\\"\\ns2 = \\\"abc\\\"\\ns3 = \
\\\"abc\\\"\\nprint(longest_common_subsequence(s1, s2, s3))  # Output: \
3\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n1. **Initialization**:\\n   - Create a 3D DP \
table `dp` where `dp[i][j][k]` stores the length of the LCS for the \
substrings `s1[0:i]`, `s2[0:j]`, and `s3[0:k]`.\\n   - Initialize the table \
with zeros.\\n\\n2. **Filling the DP Table**:\\n   - Iterate through each \
character of the strings using indices `i`, `j`, and `k`.\\n   - If the \
characters `s1[i-1]`, `s2[j-1]`, and `s3[k-1]` match, increment the value \
from the previous indices\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
             "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}], "Grid"], 
          ImageSize -> {400, Automatic}]], Annotation[#, 
         Pane[
          Grid[{{
             Style["Prompt:", Bold], 
             "Write a function to find the longest common subsequence for the \
given three string sequence."}, {
             Style["Response:", Bold], 
             "To find the longest common subsequence (LCS) among three \
strings, you can use dynamic programming. Here is a Python function to \
achieve this:\n\n```python\ndef longest_common_subsequence(s1, s2, s3):\n    \
# Get the lengths of the strings\n    len1, len2, len3 = len(s1), len(s2), \
len(s3)\n    \n    # Create a 3D DP array to store lengths of LCS\n    dp = \
[[[0] * (len3 + 1) for _ in range(len2 + 1)] for __ in range(len1 + 1)]\n    \
\n    # Build the dp array\n    for i in range(1, len1 + 1):\n        for j \
in range(1, len2 + 1):\n            for k in range(1, len3 + 1):\n            \
    if s1[i - 1] == s2[j - 1] == s3[k - 1]:\n                    dp[i][j][k] \
= dp[i - 1][j - 1][k - 1] + 1\n                else:\n                    \
dp[i][j][k] = max(dp[i - 1][j][k], dp[i][j - 1][k], dp[i][j][k - 1])\n    \n  \
  # The length of LCS will be in dp[len1][len2][len3]\n    return \
dp[len1][len2][len3]\n\n# Example usage\ns1 = \"abc\"\ns2 = \"abc\"\ns3 = \
\"abc\"\nprint(longest_common_subsequence(s1, s2, s3))  # Output: 3\n```\n\n\
### Explanation:\n1. **Initialization**:\n   - Create a 3D DP table `dp` \
where `dp[i][j][k]` stores the length of the LCS for the substrings \
`s1[0:i]`, `s2[0:j]`, and `s3[0:k]`.\n   - Initialize the table with zeros.\n\
\n2. **Filling the DP Table**:\n   - Iterate through each character of the \
strings using indices `i`, `j`, and `k`.\n   - If the characters `s1[i-1]`, \
`s2[j-1]`, and `s3[k-1]` match, increment the value from the previous \
indices"}}, Alignment -> {Left, Top}], {400, Automatic}], "Tooltip"]& ], 
