jacobsthal(n):\\n    if n == 0:\\n        return 0\\n    elif n == 1:\\n      \
  return 1\\n    else:\\n        a, b = 0, 1\\n        for _ in range(2, n + \
1):\\n            a, b = b, b + 2 * a\\n        return b\\n\\n# Example \
usage:\\nn = 5\\nprint(jacobsthal(n))  # Output will be the 5th Jacobsthal \
number\\n```\\n\\nThis function uses an iterative approach to calculate the \
nth Jacobsthal number efficiently.\""}}, 
