degrees, you must first convert it to radians using the formula:\\n\\n\\\\[ \
\\\\theta_{\\\\text{radians}} = \\\\theta_{\\\\text{degrees}} \\\\times \
\\\\frac{\\\\pi}{180} \\\\]\\n\\nHere's a Python function to calculate the \
arc length:\\n\\n```python\\nimport math\\n\\ndef \
calculate_arc_length(radius, angle_degrees):\\n    # Convert angle from \
degrees to radians\\n    angle_radians = math.radians(angle_degrees)\\n    # \
