arc_length\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# radius = 5 units, angle = 60 \
degrees\\narc_length = calculate_arc_length(5, 60)\\nprint(f\\\"The arc \
length is: {arc_length} units\\\")\\n```\\n\\nThis function takes the radius \
of the circle and the central angle in degrees as inputs, converts the angle \
to radians, and then calculates and returns the arc length.\""}}, 
