              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find the minimum difference between any two elements in a \
given array, you can follow these steps:\\n\\n1. Sort the array.\\n2. \
Initialize a variable to track the minimum difference.\\n3. Iterate through \
the sorted array, computing the difference between consecutive elements.\\n4. \
Update the minimum difference if a smaller one is found.\\n\\nHere's a Python \
function implementing the above logic:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
find_minimum_difference(arr):\\n    if len(arr) < 2:\\n        raise \
ValueError(\\\"Array must contain at least two elements to find a minimum \
difference.\\\")\\n    \\n    # Sort the array\\n    arr.sort()\\n    \\n    \
# Initialize minimum difference as a large number\\n    min_diff = \
float('inf')\\n    \\n    # Iterate and find the minimum difference between \
consecutive elements\\n    for i in range(len(arr) - 1):\\n        diff = \
arr[i + 1] - arr[i]\\n        if diff < min_diff:\\n            min_diff = \
diff\\n    \\n    return min_diff\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# arr = [3, 8, 15, \
1]\\n# print(find_minimum_difference(arr))  # Output: 2 (minimum difference \
is between 1 and 3)\\n```\\n\\nThis function first checks if the array has at \
least two elements. It then sorts the array, calculates differences between \
consecutive pairs, and updates the minimum difference found. The function \
returns the smallest difference.\""}}, 
