              "\"Write a function to find nth polite number.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"A polite number is a positive integer that can be expressed \
as the sum of two or more consecutive positive integers. All numbers except \
powers of 2 are polite numbers. Here's a Python function to find the nth \
polite number:\\n\\n```python\\ndef nth_polite_number(n):\\n    count = 0\\n  \
  num = 1\\n    while count < n:\\n        num += 1\\n        if (num & (num \
- 1)) != 0:  # Check if `num` is not a power of 2\\n            count += 1\\n \
   return num\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# Find the 5th polite \
number\\nprint(nth_polite_number(5))\\n```\\n\\nThis function increments \
numbers starting from 1, skipping powers of 2, until it finds the nth polite \
number.\""}}, GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
             "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}], "Grid"], 
          ImageSize -> {400, Automatic}]], Annotation[#, 
         Pane[
          Grid[{{
             Style["Prompt:", Bold], 
             "Write a function to find nth polite number."}, {
             Style["Response:", Bold], 
             "A polite number is a positive integer that can be expressed as \
the sum of two or more consecutive positive integers. All numbers except \
powers of 2 are polite numbers. Here's a Python function to find the nth \
polite number:\n\n```python\ndef nth_polite_number(n):\n    count = 0\n    \
num = 1\n    while count < n:\n        num += 1\n        if (num & (num - 1)) \
!= 0:  # Check if `num` is not a power of 2\n            count += 1\n    \
return num\n\n# Example usage:\n# Find the 5th polite number\n\
print(nth_polite_number(5))\n```\n\nThis function increments numbers starting \
from 1, skipping powers of 2, until it finds the nth polite number."}}, 
