              "\"To find the occurrence and position of substrings within a \
string in Python, you can write a function that utilizes string methods to \
search for each occurrence of the substring and records its position. Here's \
a Python function that accomplishes this task:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
find_substring_occurrences(main_string, substring):\\n    occurrences = []\\n \
   start = 0\\n    \\n    while True:\\n        # Find the start index of the \
substring\\n        start = main_string.find(substring, start)\\n        \\n  \
      # If find() returns -1, there are no more occurrences\\n        if \
start == -1:\\n            break\\n        \\n        # Append the position \
to the list\\n        occurrences.append(start)\\n        \\n        # Move \
to the next character after the current found position\\n        start += \
1\\n    \\n    return occurrences\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nmain_string = \
\\\"This is a test string. Testing is essential for tests.\\\"\\nsubstring = \
\\\"test\\\"\\npositions = find_substring_occurrences(main_string, substring)\
\\nprint(\\\"Occurrences of substring:\\\", positions)\\n```\\n\\n### \
Explanation:\\n- The function `find_substring_occurrences` takes two \
parameters: `main_string` (the string to search within) and `substring` (the \
substring to find).\\n- An empty list `occurrences` is initialized to store \
the positions of each occurrence.\\n- A `while` loop is used to repeatedly \
search for the substring starting from the last found position.\\n- The \
`find` method returns the lowest index where the substring is found, or `-1` \
if it is not found.\\n- When an occurrence is found, its index is appended to \
the `occurrences` list.\\n- The `start` variable is incremented by 1 to \
continue searching for subsequent occurrences.\\n- The loop breaks when no \
more occurrences are found (`start == -1`).\\n\\nThis function will return a \
list of zero-based indices indicating where each occurrence of the substring \
starts within the main string.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
