              "\"Certainly! To find the sum of non-repeated elements in an \
array, you can follow these steps in Python:\\n\\n1. Use a dictionary to \
count the occurrences of each element in the array.\\n2. Iterate through the \
dictionary and sum the elements that appear exactly once.\\n\\nHere's the \
Python function implementing these steps:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
sum_of_non_repeated_elements(arr):\\n    # Step 1: Count the occurrences of \
each element\\n    element_count = {}\\n    for num in arr:\\n        if num \
in element_count:\\n            element_count[num] += 1\\n        else:\\n    \
        element_count[num] = 1\\n    \\n    # Step 2: Sum the elements that \
appear exactly once\\n    non_repeated_sum = sum(num for num, count in \
element_count.items() if count == 1)\\n    \\n    return \
non_repeated_sum\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# array = [4, 5, 7, 4, 5, 8]\\n# \
print(sum_of_non_repeated_elements(array))  # Output: 15 (7 + \
8)\\n```\\n\\nThis function will efficiently compute the sum of all \
non-repeated elements in the given array.\""}}, 
