grouping consecutive duplicate elements into sublists. Below is a Python \
function that accomplishes this task:\n\n```python\ndef \
pack_consecutive_duplicates(lst):\n    if not lst:\n        return []\n\n    \
packed = []\n    current_sublist = [lst[0]]\n\n    for element in lst[1:]:\n  \
      if element == current_sublist[-1]:\n            \
