**Check for an empty list**: If the input list is empty, return an empty list \
immediately.\n2. **Initialize `packed` and `current_sublist`**: \n   - \
`packed` will hold the final list of sublists.\n   - `current_sublist` starts \
with the first element of the list to begin grouping.\n3. **Iterate through \
the list**: \n   - For each element, check if it matches the last element of \
`current_sublist`.\n   - If it matches, append it to `current_sublist`.\n   - \
