one element from each tuple.\n- **`sum(comb)`**: For each combination \
generated, we calculate the sum.\n- **`set()`**: We use a set to store sums \
to automatically handle duplicates.\n- **`sorted()`**: Finally, we sort the \
sums to return them in ascending order.\n\nThe example with `tuple_list = \
