              "\"To find the sum of all odd-length subarrays of a given \
array, you can iterate over all possible subarrays and check if their length \
is odd. If it is, add the sum of that subarray to a total sum. Here's a \
Python function to achieve this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
sum_odd_length_subarrays(arr):\\n    n = len(arr)\\n    total_sum = 0\\n    \
\\n    # Iterate over all possible subarray starting points\\n    for start \
in range(n):\\n        # Iterate over all possible subarray ending points\\n  \
      for end in range(start, n):\\n            # Check if the length of the \
subarray is odd\\n            if (end - start + 1) % 2 == 1:\\n               \
 # Add the sum of this subarray to the total sum\\n                total_sum \
+= sum(arr[start:end + 1])\\n    \\n    return total_sum\\n\\n# Example \
usage:\\narr = [1, 4, 2, 5, 3]\\nprint(sum_odd_length_subarrays(arr))  # \
Output: 58\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n1. **Outer Loop (`start`)**: Iterate \
over each possible starting point of a subarray.\\n2. **Inner Loop (`end`)**: \
Iterate over each possible ending point of a subarray starting from the \
current `start`.\\n3. **Odd Length Check**: Check if the length of the \
current subarray (`end - start + 1`) is odd.\\n4. **Sum Calculation**: If the \
subarray length is odd, calculate its sum and add it to \
`total_sum`.\\n\\nThis function will correctly compute the sum of all \
odd-length subarrays.\""}}, 
