              "\"To convert an RGB color to an HSV color, you can use the \
following function in Python:\\n\\n```python\\ndef rgb_to_hsv(r, g, b):\\n    \
# Convert RGB values from 0-255 to 0-1 range\\n    r, g, b = r / 255.0, g / \
255.0, b / 255.0\\n    \\n    # Calculate the maximum and minimum values \
among the RGB components\\n    max_val = max(r, g, b)\\n    min_val = min(r, \
g, b)\\n    delta = max_val - min_val\\n\\n    # Calculate Hue\\n    if delta \
== 0:\\n        h = 0\\n    elif max_val == r:\\n        h = (60 * ((g - b) / \
delta) + 360) % 360\\n    elif max_val == g:\\n        h = (60 * ((b - r) / \
delta) + 120) % 360\\n    elif max_val == b:\\n        h = (60 * ((r - g) / \
delta) + 240) % 360\\n\\n    # Calculate Saturation\\n    s = 0 if max_val == \
0 else (delta / max_val)\\n\\n    # Calculate Value\\n    v = max_val\\n\\n   \
 # Return HSV values, h in range [0, 360], s and v in range [0, 1]\\n    \
return h, s, v\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# rgb = (255, 0, 0)  # Red color\\n# \
hsv = rgb_to_hsv(*rgb)\\n# print(hsv)  # Output should be (0.0, 1.0, \
1.0)\\n```\\n\\nThis function first normalizes the RGB values to the range \
0-1, then calculates the hue, saturation, and value (brightness) based on the \
formulas for converting RGB to HSV. The hue is adjusted to be between 0 and \
360 degrees, while the saturation and value are between 0 and 1.\""}}, 
