tuple, you can use Python's `ast.literal_eval` function from the `ast` \
module, which safely evaluates a string containing a Python literal \
expression. Here's how you can write a function to achieve this:\n\n```python\
\nimport ast\n\ndef convert_tuple_string_to_int_tuple(tuple_string):\n    \
try:\n        # Safely evaluate the string as a Python literal\n        \
result = ast.literal_eval(tuple_string)\n        # Check if the result is a \
