             Style["Response:", Bold], 
             "To locate the right insertion point for a specified value in a \
sorted list, you can use the `bisect` module in Python, specifically the \
`bisect_right` function. This function returns the index where the specified \
value should be inserted to maintain sorted order, such that if the value is \
already present, it is inserted after the existing values.\n\nHere's a sample \
function demonstrating how to use `bisect_right`:\n\n```python\nimport bisect\
\n\ndef find_right_insertion_point(sorted_list, value):\n    # Use \
bisect_right to find the right insertion point\n    return \
bisect.bisect_right(sorted_list, value)\n\n# Example usage:\nsorted_list = \
[1, 2, 4, 4, 5]\nvalue_to_insert = 4\ninsertion_point = \
