match_a_followed_by_anything_ending_in_b(s):\\n    # Define the regular \
expression pattern\\n    # 'a' followed by any characters (.*) ending with \
'b'\\n    pattern = r'a.*b$'\\n    \\n    # Use re.match to check if the \
whole string matches the pattern\\n    if re.match(pattern, s):\\n        \
return True\\n    else:\\n        return False\\n\\n# Example \
usage:\\nprint(match_a_followed_by_anything_ending_in_b(\\\"acb\\\"))  # True\
\\nprint(match_a_followed_by_anything_ending_in_b(\\\"a123b\\\"))  # \
True\\nprint(match_a_followed_by_anything_ending_in_b(\\\"ab\\\"))  # \
True\\nprint(match_a_followed_by_anything_ending_in_b(\\\"abc\\\"))  # \
False\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- `r'a.*b$'`: This regular expression \
pattern is used to find a string that:\\n  - Starts with `a`.\\n  - Has any \
number of any characters in between (`.*`).\\n  - Ends with `b` (`b$` \
indicates that `b` must be at the end of the string).\\n- `re.match()` checks \
if the entire string matches the pattern. If it does, the function returns \
`True`; otherwise, it returns `False`.\""}}, 
