             "To check if two lists of tuples are identical, you can create a \
function in Python that compares both lists for equality. Here's a simple \
function to achieve this:\n\n```python\ndef are_lists_identical(list1, \
list2):\n    # Check if the lengths of the lists are the same\n    if \
len(list1) != len(list2):\n        return False\n    \n    # Check if all \
elements in both lists are the same and in the same order\n    for tuple1, \
tuple2 in zip(list1, list2):\n        if tuple1 != tuple2:\n            \
