algorithm. This algorithm efficiently sorts the array in a single pass with \
O(n) time complexity and O(1) space complexity. Here's the implementation in \
Python:\n\n```python\ndef sort_012_array(arr):\n    low = 0\n    mid = 0\n    \
high = len(arr) - 1\n    \n    while mid <= high:\n        if arr[mid] == 0:\n\
            arr[low], arr[mid] = arr[mid], arr[low]\n            low += 1\n   \
         mid += 1\n        elif arr[mid] == 1:\n            mid += 1\n        \
else:  # arr[mid] == 2\n            arr[mid], arr[high] = arr[high], arr[mid]\
\n            high -= 1\n\n# Example usage:\narr = [2, 0, 1, 2, 1, 0]\n\
sort_012_array(arr)\nprint(arr)  # Output will be: [0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2]\n```\n\n\
