must contain at least one lowercase letter.\\n4. It must contain at least one \
digit.\\n5. It must contain at least one special character (e.g., !, @, #, $, \
%, ^, &, *, etc.).\\n\\nHere's a Python function that checks if a password \
meets these criteria:\\n\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef \
is_valid_password(password):\\n    # Check if password is at least 8 \
characters long\\n    if len(password) < 8:\\n        return False\\n\\n    # \
Check for at least one uppercase letter\\n    if not re.search(r'[A-Z]', \
password):\\n        return False\\n\\n    # Check for at least one lowercase \
letter\\n    if not re.search(r'[a-z]', password):\\n        return \
False\\n\\n    # Check for at least one digit\\n    if not \
re.search(r'[0-9]', password):\\n        return False\\n\\n    # Check for at \
least one special character\\n    if not \
re.search(r'[!@#$%^&*(),.?\\\":{}|<>]', password):\\n        return \
False\\n\\n    # If all conditions are met, the password is valid\\n    \
return True\\n\\n# Example usage:\\n# \
print(is_valid_password(\\\"Password123!\\\"))  # Should return True\\n```\\n\
\\nThis function uses regular expressions to check for the presence of \
uppercase letters, lowercase letters, digits, and special characters. If the \
password satisfies all these conditions, the function returns `True`; \
otherwise, it returns `False`.\""}}, 
