\"apple\"\n```\n\n### Explanation:\n1. **Count Frequencies**: We iterate over \
the given sequence and populate a dictionary where keys are the strings and \
values are their counts.\n2. **Sort by Frequency**: We convert the dictionary \
into a list of tuples and sort it by the frequency of the strings in \
descending order.\n3. **Return the Result**: If there are at least two \
