Here's a Python function to accomplish this:\n\n```python\ndef \
count_equal_pairs(arr):\n    # Dictionary to store the frequency of each \
element\n    frequency = {}\n    \n    # Count the frequency of each element \
in the array\n    for num in arr:\n        if num in frequency:\n            \
frequency[num] += 1\n        else:\n            frequency[num] = 1\n    \n    \
# Calculate the number of pairs\n    pair_count = 0\n    for count in \
