              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To solve the problem of finding the length of the subarray \
with the maximum sum, we can use a modified version of Kadane's algorithm. \
Kadane's algorithm is typically used to find the maximum sum of a contiguous \
subarray, but we can adapt it to also track the length of the subarray that \
yields this maximum sum.\\n\\nHere's how you can implement this in Python:\\n\
\\n```python\\ndef max_sum_subarray_length(arr):\\n    # Initialize variables\
\\n    max_sum = float('-inf')  # This will store the maximum sum found\\n    \
current_sum = 0          # This will store the current sum while iterating\\n \
   max_length = 0           # This will store the length of the subarray with \
maximum sum\\n    current_length = 0       # This will store the current \
length of the subarray\\n\\n    for num in arr:\\n        # Add current \
element to current sum\\n        current_sum += num\\n        current_length \
+= 1\\n\\n        # Check if we found a new maximum sum\\n        if \
current_sum > max_sum:\\n            max_sum = current_sum\\n            \
max_length = current_length\\n        elif current_sum == max_sum:\\n         \
   # If current sum is equal to the max sum, take the longer subarray\\n      \
      max_length = max(max_length, current_length)\\n\\n        # If current \
sum becomes negative, reset it\\n        if current_sum < 0:\\n            \
current_sum = 0\\n            current_length = 0\\n\\n    return \
max_length\\n\\n# Example usage:\\narr = [1, -2, 3, 4, -1, 2, 1, -5, \
4]\\nprint(max_sum_subarray_length(arr))  # Output will be 4, for subarray \
[3, 4, -1, 2]\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n\\n- **max_sum**: Keeps track of \
the maximum sum encountered so far.\\n- **current_sum**: Accumulates the sum \
of the current subarray.\\n- **max_length**: Records the length of the \
subarray with the maximum sum.\\n- **current_length**: Keeps track of the \
current subarray length.\\n\\nAs we iterate through the array:\\n- We update \
the current sum and increment the current length.\\n- If the current sum \
exceeds the max sum, we update the max sum and set max length to the current \
length.\\n- If the current sum equals the max sum, we update max length to \
the maximum of\""}}, 
