              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find the cube sum of the first \\\\( n \\\\) odd natural \
numbers, we can use the fact that the \\\\( k \\\\)-th odd natural number can \
be represented as \\\\( 2k - 1 \\\\). Therefore, the first \\\\( n \\\\) odd \
natural numbers are \\\\( 1, 3, 5, \\\\ldots, (2n-1) \\\\).\\n\\nThe function \
will sum the cubes of these numbers. Here is the Python function to achieve \
this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef cube_sum_of_odd_numbers(n):\\n    # Initialize the \
sum\\n    cube_sum = 0\\n\\n    # Loop through the first n odd natural \
numbers\\n    for i in range(1, n + 1):\\n        # Calculate the i-th odd \
number\\n        odd_number = 2 * i - 1\\n        # Add its cube to the \
sum\\n        cube_sum += odd_number ** 3\\n    \\n    return cube_sum\\n\\n# \
Example usage:\\nn = 5\\nprint(cube_sum_of_odd_numbers(n))  # Output for \
first 5 odd numbers: 1^3 + 3^3 + 5^3 + 7^3 + 9^3\\n```\\n\\nThis function \
calculates and returns the sum of the cubes of the first \\\\( n \\\\) odd \
natural numbers.\""}}, 
