comprehensions to create two separate lists: `odd_elements` for odd numbers \
and `even_elements` for even numbers.\n\n2. **Reorder the List:**\n   - \
Concatenate `odd_elements` with `even_elements` to get a new list where all \
odd numbers come before any even numbers.\n\n3. **Retrieve the k-th \
