              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To solve the problem of finding the minimum number of \
platforms required at a railway or bus station, you need to consider the \
arrival and departure times of the trains or buses. The goal is to determine \
the peak number of vehicles present at the station at any one \
time.\\n\\nHere's a Python function to achieve this:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
find_minimum_platforms(arrival, departure):\\n    # Sort the arrival and \
departure times\\n    arrival.sort()\\n    departure.sort()\\n\\n    n = \
len(arrival)\\n    platform_needed = 0\\n    max_platforms = 0\\n    i = 0  # \
Pointer to traverse arrival array\\n    j = 0  # Pointer to traverse \
departure array\\n\\n    # Traverse through all events (arrival or departure)\
\\n    while i < n and j < n:\\n        # If next event in sorted order is an \
arrival, increment count of platforms needed\\n        if arrival[i] < \
departure[j]:\\n            platform_needed += 1\\n            i += 1\\n\\n   \
         # Update the result if needed\\n            if platform_needed > \
max_platforms:\\n                max_platforms = platform_needed\\n        \
else:\\n            # Else decrement count of platforms needed\\n            \
platform_needed -= 1\\n            j += 1\\n\\n    return \
max_platforms\\n\\n# Example usage:\\narrival_times = [900, 940, 950, 1100, \
1500, 1800]\\ndeparture_times = [910, 1200, 1120, 1130, 1900, \
2000]\\nprint(find_minimum_platforms(arrival_times, departure_times))  # \
Output: 3\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n1. **Sort the Timings**: Start by \
sorting the arrival and departure times.\\n2. **Two Pointers Technique**: Use \
two pointers, one for the arrival array (`i`) and another for the departure \
array (`j`).\\n3. **Iterate Over Events**: Traverse through the sorted times:\
\\n   - If the next event is an arrival (i.e., `arrival[i] < departure[j]`), \
it means a new platform is needed, so increment the count of platforms.\\n   \
- If the next event is a departure, it means a platform is freed, so \
decrement the count of platforms.\\n4. **Track Maximum Platforms**: Update \
the maximum number of platforms needed during the traversal whenever the \
current count of platforms exceeds the previously recorded maximum.\\n5. \
**Return the Maximum**:\""}}, 
