              "\"To find the sum of the inverses of the divisors of a given \
integer \\\\( n \\\\), you can follow these steps:\\n\\n1. Find all the \
divisors of \\\\( n \\\\).\\n2. Compute the inverse (reciprocal) of each \
divisor.\\n3. Sum up all these inverses.\\n\\nHere's a Python function that \
implements this logic:\\n\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_inverse_of_divisors(n):\\n \
   # Initialize the sum\\n    inverse_sum = 0.0\\n    # Find all divisors of \
