divisors of {n} is {result}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n\\n- The \
function iterates over all integers from 1 to \\\\( n \\\\).\\n- For each \
integer \\\\( i \\\\), it checks if \\\\( i \\\\) is a divisor of \\\\( n \
\\\\) using the modulus operator (`n % i == 0`).\\n- If \\\\( i \\\\) is a \
divisor, its inverse \\\\( \\\\frac{1}{i} \\\\) is added to the cumulative \
sum `inverse_sum`.\\n- Finally, the function returns the total sum of the \
inverses of the divisors of \\\\( n \\\\).\""}}, 
