range(1, n + 1):\\n        # Check if i is a factor of n and if it is odd\\n  \
      if n % i == 0 and i % 2 != 0:\\n            # Add it to the sum\\n      \
      odd_factors_sum += i\\n    \\n    return odd_factors_sum\\n\\n# Example \
usage:\\nnumber = 36\\nprint(f\\\"Sum of odd factors of {number} is \
{sum_of_odd_factors(number)}\\\")\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n\\n1. \
**Initialize** a variable `odd_factors_sum` to store the sum of odd \
factors.\\n2. **Iterate** through all numbers from 1 to `n` (inclusive).\\n3. \
For each number `i`, check if it is a **factor** of `n` (`n % i == 0`).\\n4. \
Check if the factor `i` is **odd** (`i % 2 != 0`).\\n5. If both conditions \
are satisfied, **add** `i` to `odd_factors_sum`.\\n6. **Return** the total \
sum of odd factors.\\n\\nThis function will efficiently compute the sum of \
all odd factors of the given number `n`.\""}}, 
