              "\"To find the minimum adjacent swaps required to sort a binary \
array (containing only 0s and 1s), you can use the following \
approach:\\n\\n1. **Count the number of 0s**: Determine how many 0s need to \
be on the left side of the sorted array. \\n\\n2. **Calculate swaps for two \
scenarios**:\\n   - **Move all 0s to the left**: Count the number of 1s \
before each 0 as you traverse the array from left to right. This count gives \
the number of swaps needed to move all 0s to the left.\\n   - **Move all 1s \
to the left**: Similarly, count the number of 0s before each 1 as you \
traverse the array. This count gives the swaps needed to move all 1s to the \
left.\\n   \\n3. **Take the minimum**: The minimum of these two counts will \
be the minimum swaps needed.\\n\\nHere's how you can implement this in \
Python:\\n\\n```python\\ndef min_swaps_to_sort_binary_array(arr):\\n    # \
Count the number of 0s\\n    count_0 = arr.count(0)\\n    \\n    # Initialize \
swap counts\\n    swaps_with_0s_left = 0\\n    swaps_with_1s_left = 0\\n    \
\\n    # To calculate swaps_with_0s_left, count 1s before each 0\\n    \
ones_before = 0\\n    for num in arr:\\n        if num == 0:\\n            \
swaps_with_0s_left += ones_before\\n        else:\\n            ones_before \
+= 1\\n    \\n    # To calculate swaps_with_1s_left, count 0s before each \
1\\n    zeros_before = 0\\n    for num in arr:\\n        if num == 1:\\n      \
      swaps_with_1s_left += zeros_before\\n        else:\\n            \
zeros_before += 1\\n    \\n    # Return the minimum of the two scenarios\\n   \
 return min(swaps_with_0s_left, swaps_with_1s_left)\\n\\n# Example \
usage:\\nbinary_array = [1, 0, 1, 0, 1, \
0]\\nprint(min_swaps_to_sort_binary_array(binary_array))  # Output: \
3\\n```\\n\\nThis function calculates and returns the minimum number of \
adjacent swaps required to sort the binary array.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
             "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}}], "Grid"], 
