              "\"To check if a given string ends with only alphanumeric \
characters using regex, you can use the `re` module in Python. Here's a \
function that accomplishes this:\\n\\n```python\\nimport re\\n\\ndef \
ends_with_alphanumeric(s):\\n    # Define a regex pattern that matches a \
string ending with alphanumeric characters\\n    pattern = r'[a-zA-Z0-9]$'\\n \
   \\n    # Use re.search to check if the pattern is found at the end of the \
string\\n    if re.search(pattern, s):\\n        return True\\n    return \
False\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nprint(ends_with_alphanumeric(\\\"Hello123\\\")) \
 # True\\nprint(ends_with_alphanumeric(\\\"Hello!\\\"))    # \
False\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- The regex pattern `[a-zA-Z0-9]$` is \
used to match any alphanumeric character (`a-z`, `A-Z`, `0-9`) at the end of \
the string (`$` denotes the end of the string).\\n- `re.search(pattern, s)` \
returns a match object if the pattern is found; otherwise, it returns `None`.\
\\n- The function returns `True` if the string ends with an alphanumeric \
character and `False` otherwise.\""}}, 
