\n# Example usage:\nprint(ends_with_alphanumeric(\"Hello123\"))  # True\n\
print(ends_with_alphanumeric(\"Hello!\"))    # False\n```\n\n### Explanation:\
\n- The regex pattern `[a-zA-Z0-9]$` is used to match any alphanumeric \
character (`a-z`, `A-Z`, `0-9`) at the end of the string (`$` denotes the end \
of the string).\n- `re.search(pattern, s)` returns a match object if the \
