              "\"To find the occurrences of the n most common words in a \
given text, we can write a Python function that follows these steps:\\n\\n1. \
Tokenize the text into words.\\n2. Normalize the words to ensure consistent \
comparison (e.g., convert to lowercase).\\n3. Count the frequency of each \
word.\\n4. Identify the n most common words and their counts.\\n\\nHere's a \
function implementing these steps using the `collections.Counter` \
class:\\n\\n```python\\nfrom collections import Counter\\nimport re\\n\\ndef \
find_most_common_words(text, n):\\n    # Use a regular expression to find \
words and normalize to lowercase\\n    words = re.findall(r'\\\\w+', \
text.lower())\\n    \\n    # Count occurrences of each word\\n    word_counts \
= Counter(words)\\n    \\n    # Get the n most common words and their \
counts\\n    most_common_words = word_counts.most_common(n)\\n    \\n    \
return most_common_words\\n\\n# Example usage:\\ntext = \\\"This is a sample \
text. This text has some words. Some words appear more than once.\\\"\\nn = 3\
\\nprint(find_most_common_words(text, n))\\n```\\n\\n### Explanation:\\n- \
**Regular Expression `\\\\w+`**: This captures sequences of word characters \
(letters and digits), effectively tokenizing the text into words.\\n- \
**`text.lower()`**: Converts the text to lowercase to ensure that word \
comparison is case-insensitive.\\n- **`Counter(words)`**: Creates a counter \
object that counts the occurrences of each word.\\n- \
**`word_counts.most_common(n)`**: Returns a list of tuples with the n most \
common words and their counts.\\n\\nThis function will return the n most \
common words in the text along with how many times they appear.\""}}, 
