create a function that utilizes `map` to repeat the printing operation. \
However, `map` is generally used for transforming data, not for executing \
actions with side effects like printing. Nevertheless, you can use it \
creatively to achieve the desired outcome:\n\n```python\ndef \
print_list_n_times(lst, n):\n    # Create a lambda function that prints the \
list\n    print_function = lambda _: print(lst)\n    \n    # Use map to apply \
the print_function n times\n    list(map(print_function, range(n)))\n\n# \
Example usage:\nmy_list = [1, 2, 3]\nprint_list_n_times(my_list, 3)\n```\n\n\
