              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find the sum of the first even and the first odd number \
in a given list, you can follow these steps in a Python \
function:\\n\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_first_even_and_odd(numbers):\\n    \
first_even = None\\n    first_odd = None\\n\\n    for num in numbers:\\n      \
  if first_even is None and num % 2 == 0:\\n            first_even = num\\n   \
     if first_odd is None and num % 2 != 0:\\n            first_odd = num\\n  \
      # If both are found, we can break out of the loop early\\n        if \
first_even is not None and first_odd is not None:\\n            break\\n\\n   \
 # Return the sum if both numbers are found\\n    if first_even is not None \
and first_odd is not None:\\n        return first_even + first_odd\\n    \
else:\\n        return None  # Return None if either of the numbers is not \
found\\n\\n# Example usage:\\nnumbers = [5, 3, 8, 4, 6]\\nresult = \
sum_of_first_even_and_odd(numbers)\\nprint(result)  # Output will be 13 (5 + \
8)\\n```\\n\\nThis function iterates through the list once, identifying the \
first even and first odd numbers, and calculates their sum if both are found. \
If either is not found, it returns `None`.\""}}, 
            GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
            AutoDelete -> False, 
            GridBoxItemSize -> {
