given array with no adjacent elements.\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To solve this problem, you can use dynamic programming. The \
idea is to iterate through the array and keep track of the maximum sum of \
subsequences up to each element, ensuring that no two adjacent elements are \
included in the sum. Here's a Python function to achieve this:\\n\\n```python\
\\ndef max_sum_no_adjacent(arr):\\n    if not arr:\\n        return 0\\n    \
if len(arr) == 1:\\n        return arr[0]\\n    \\n    # Create an array to \
store the maximum sum at each index\\n    n = len(arr)\\n    max_sum = [0] * \
n\\n    \\n    # Initialize the first two values\\n    max_sum[0] = arr[0]\\n \
   max_sum[1] = max(arr[0], arr[1])\\n    \\n    # Fill the max_sum array\\n  \
  for i in range(2, n):\\n        # Either take the current element and add \
it to the max_sum[i-2]\\n        # or skip the current element and take the \
max_sum[i-1]\\n        max_sum[i] = max(arr[i] + max_sum[i-2], \
max_sum[i-1])\\n    \\n    # The last element contains the result\\n    \
return max_sum[-1]\\n\\n# Example usage:\\narr = [3, 2, 7, 10]\\nresult = \
max_sum_no_adjacent(arr)\\nprint(result)  # Output: 13\\n```\\n\\n### \
Explanation:\\n1. **Base Cases**: \\n   - If the array is empty, the maximum \
sum is 0.\\n   - If the array has one element, the maximum sum is the value \
of that element.\\n\\n2. **Dynamic Programming Array**:\\n   - `max_sum[i]` \
represents the maximum sum of subsequences from the start of the array up to \
index `i`, without taking adjacent elements.\\n\\n3. **Recurrence Relation**:\
\\n   - For each element `arr[i]`, decide whether to include it in the \
sum:\\n     - If included, add it to `max_sum[i-2]` (since `arr[i-1]` cannot \
be included).\\n     - If not included, carry forward the maximum sum up to \
`i-1`, i.e., `max_sum[i-1]`.\\n   - The formula is: `max_sum[i] = max(arr[i] \
+ max_sum[i-2], max_sum[i-1])`.\\n\\n4. **Result**:\\n   - The last entry \
in\""}}, GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
