Specifically, you can use the `sorted()` function with a custom key. Here's \
the function that accomplishes this task:\\n\\n```python\\ndef \
sort_by_last_element(tuples_list):\\n    # Use the sorted function with a \
lambda function as the key\\n    # The lambda function extracts the last \
element from each tuple for comparison\\n    return sorted(tuples_list, \
