Explanation:\\n- The function `extract_continuous_elements` takes three \
parameters: the list `lst`, the `start_index` from where to begin extraction, \
and `num_elements`, the number of elements to extract.\\n- It checks if the \
provided `start_index` and `num_elements` are valid (i.e., `start_index` \
should not be negative, and it should be within the list bounds; \
`num_elements` should be positive).\\n- The function uses list slicing to \
extract elements: `lst[start_index:start_index + num_elements]`. This will \
automatically adjust if `num_elements` goes beyond the end of the list, only \
returning elements up to the end of the list.\\n- If the conditions are not \
