hour.\\n\\n2. **Speed on downhill slopes:**\\n   - It is 12 miles per hour \
faster than on flat sand.\\n   - Speed = 60 + 12 = 72 miles per hour.\\n\\n3. \
**Speed on uphill slopes:**\\n   - It is 18 miles per hour slower than on \
flat sand.\\n   - Speed = 60 - 18 = 42 miles per hour.\\n\\n4. **Average \
Speed Calculation:**\\n   - Since Conner spends one-third of the time on each \
terrain, the average speed \\\\( v_{\\\\text{avg}} \\\\) is given by the \
formula:\\n     \\\\[\\n     v_{\\\\text{avg}} = \\\\frac{1}{3} \\\\times \
\\\\text{Speed on flat sand} + \\\\frac{1}{3} \\\\times \\\\text{Speed on \
downhill} + \\\\frac{1}{3} \\\\times \\\\text{Speed on uphill}\\n     \
\\\\]\\n   - Plug in the values:\\n     \\\\[\\n     v_{\\\\text{avg}} = \
\\\\frac{1}{3} \\\\times 60 + \\\\frac{1}{3} \\\\times 72 + \\\\frac{1}{3} \\\
