$4.\\n   - Therefore, the revenue from one pie is \\\\( 3 \\\\times 4 = 12 \\\
\\) dollars.\\n\\n2. **Determine the Cost per Pie:**\\n   - The cost to \
create one pie is $0.5.\\n\\n3. **Calculate the Profit per Pie:**\\n   - The \
profit from one pie is the revenue minus the cost.\\n   - Profit per pie = \
