hour.\\n\\n5. **Calculate the Total Profit for One Hour:**\\n   - Total \
profit in one hour = Number of pies made \[Times] Profit per pie\\n   - Total \
profit = \\\\( 12 \\\\times 11.5 = 138 \\\\) dollars.\\n\\nTherefore, the \
bakery would make $138 in profit if it sells all the pie pieces in one \
hour.\""}}, GridBoxAlignment -> {"Columns" -> {{Left}}, "Rows" -> {{Top}}}, 
