              StyleBox["\"Prompt:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"A rectangular plot of private property is fenced in by a \
chain-link fence. The long sides of the plot are three times the length of \
the short sides. One short side of the fence is rusted from being hit by a \
sprinkler and needs to be replaced. If all the sides of the fence together \
are 640 feet long, how many feet of fence need to be replaced?\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To solve this problem, we need to find the length of one of \
the short sides of the rectangular plot, as that will be the side that needs \
replacement.\\n\\nLet's denote the length of the short side of the rectangle \
as \\\\( x \\\\). According to the problem, the long sides are three times \
the length of the short sides, so the length of the long side is \\\\( 3x \
\\\\).\\n\\nThe perimeter of the rectangle, which is the total length of the \
fence, is given by the formula:\\n\\\\[\\n2(\\\\text{short side}) + \
2(\\\\text{long side}) = 2x + 2(3x)\\n\\\\]\\n\\nThis simplifies \
to:\\n\\\\[\\n2x + 6x = 8x\\n\\\\]\\n\\nWe know the total perimeter is 640 \
feet, so:\\n\\\\[\\n8x = 640\\n\\\\]\\n\\nTo find \\\\( x \\\\), divide both \
sides by 8:\\n\\\\[\\nx = \\\\frac{640}{8} = 80\\n\\\\]\\n\\nSo, the length \
of the short side is 80 feet. Since only one short side needs to be replaced, \
the amount of fence that needs replacement is:\\n\\\\[\\n\\\\boxed{80 \
\\\\text{ feet}}\\n\\\\]\""}}, 
