the price of 1 orange is $0.50. How much does 1 apple cost if your total bill \
was $66?\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To solve this problem, we need to determine the cost of each \
fruit type and find how much one apple costs.\\n\\nFirst, let's define the \
number of each type of fruit you bought:\\n- You bought 36 fruits evenly \
split between oranges, apples, and watermelons.\\n- Therefore, you bought 12 \
oranges, 12 apples, and 12 watermelons.\\n\\nThe total cost of the fruits was \
$66.\\n\\nCalculate the cost of the oranges:\\n- Each orange costs $0.50.\\n- \
So, the cost for 12 oranges is \\\\( 12 \\\\times 0.50 = 6 \\\\) \
dollars.\\n\\nNext, let \\\\( x \\\\) be the cost of one apple. Since 4 \
apples cost the same as 1 watermelon, 1 watermelon costs \\\\( 4x \
\\\\).\\n\\nNow, calculate the cost of 12 apples and 12 watermelons:\\n- The \
cost of 12 apples is \\\\( 12x \\\\).\\n- The cost of 12 watermelons is \\\\( \
12 \\\\times 4x = 48x \\\\).\\n\\nThe total cost equation is:\\n\\\\[\\n6 + \
12x + 48x = 66\\n\\\\]\\n\\nCombine the terms involving \\\\( x \
\\\\):\\n\\\\[\\n6 + 60x = 66\\n\\\\]\\n\\nSubtract 6 from both sides to \
isolate the term with \\\\( x \\\\):\\n\\\\[\\n60x = 60\\n\\\\]\\n\\nDivide \
