altogether were at the gathering?\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find the total number of people at the gathering, we can \
use the principle of inclusion-exclusion. Let \\\\( A \\\\) be the set of \
people who took wine and \\\\( B \\\\) be the set of people who took soda.\\n\
\\nAccording to the problem:\\n- \\\\( |A| = 26 \\\\) (people took wine)\\n- \
\\\\( |B| = 22 \\\\) (people took soda)\\n- \\\\( |A \\\\cap B| = 17 \\\\) \
