peanuts to oil is 8 ounces of peanuts to 2 ounces of oil. This can be \
simplified to 4 ounces of peanuts to 1 ounce of oil.\\n\\nThe total weight of \
the peanut butter batch is 20 ounces. Let's represent the amount of peanuts \
used as \\\\( x \\\\) ounces, and the amount of oil used as \\\\( y \\\\) \
ounces. We know:\\n\\n\\\\[ x + y = 20 \\\\]\\n\\nFrom the simplified ratio, \
we have:\\n\\n\\\\[ \\\\frac{x}{y} = 4 \\\\]\\n\\nThis implies:\\n\\n\\\\[ x \
= 4y \\\\]\\n\\nSubstitute \\\\( x = 4y \\\\) into the equation \\\\( x + y = \
20 \\\\):\\n\\n\\\\[ 4y + y = 20 \\\\]\\n\\n\\\\[ 5y = 20 \\\\]\\n\\nSolve \
for \\\\( y \\\\):\\n\\n\\\\[ y = \\\\frac{20}{5} = 4 \\\\]\\n\\nThus, Sonja \
used 4 ounces of oil in her last batch of peanut butter.\\n\\n**Final Answer: \
4 ounces**\""}}, 
