hours at a speed of 30 kilometers per hour. \\n   - Distance traveled = Speed \
\[Times] Time = 30 km/h \[Times] 20 h = 600 km.\\n\\n2. **Destination \
distance:**\\n   - The 600 km represents halfway to the destination.\\n   - \
Therefore, the total distance to the destination is twice this initial \
distance:\\n     \\\\[\\n     \\\\text{Total distance} = 2 \\\\times 600 \
\\\\text{ km} = 1200 \\\\text{ km}.\\n     \\\\]\\n\\n3. **New position after \
the storm:**\\n   - The Skipper found that he was only one-third of the way \
to his destination after the storm.\\n   - One-third of the total distance \
