backward:**\\n   - The ship initially traveled 600 km east.\\n   - After the \
storm, the ship is only 400 km east of the starting point.\\n   - Therefore, \
the ship was blown backward:\\n     \\\\[\\n     600 \\\\text{ km} - 400 \
\\\\text{ km} = 200 \\\\text{ km}.\\n     \\\\]\\n\\nThus, the ship was blown \
