\\\\):\\n\\n\\\\[\\nT = 2B \\\\implies 8 = 2B \\\\implies B = \
4\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNext, substitute the value of \\\\( B \\\\) and \\\\( T \\\\) \
into equation 3:\\n\\n\\\\[\\nB + L + P = 2T \\\\implies 4 + L + P = 2 \
\\\\times 8 = 16\\n\\\\]\\n\\nThis simplifies to:\\n\\n\\\\[\\nL + P = 12 \
\\\\quad \\\\text{(Equation 5)}\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNow, use equation 4 to express \
\\\\( P \\\\):\\n\\n\\\\[\\nP = \\\\frac{1}{6}(B + L + \
