equation:\\n\\n\\\\[\\nP = \\\\frac{1}{6}(4 + L + P)\\n\\\\]\\n\\nMultiply \
both sides by 6 to clear the fraction:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n6P = 4 + L + P\\n\\\\]\\n\
\\nSimplify:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n5P = 4 + L\\n\\\\]\\n\\nSolve for \\\\( L \\\\):\\n\
\\n\\\\[\\nL = 5P - 4 \\\\quad \\\\text{(Equation 6)}\\n\\\\]\\n\\nNow, \
substitute equation 6 into equation 5:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n(5P - 4) + P = 12\\n\\\\]\
\\n\\nSimplify:\\n\\n\\\\[\\n6P - 4 = 12\\n\\\\]\\n\\nAdd 4 to both sides:\\n\
\\n\\\\[\\n6P = 16\\n\\\\]\\n\\nDivide by\""}}, 
