children, except for 2, has the same number of children as Max does, we can \
assume that the remaining 6 children each have 8 children of their own.\n\n1. \
Compute the number of grandchildren from the 6 children who have 8 children \
each:\n   \\[\n   6 \\times 8 = 48\n   \\]\n\n2. Compute the number of \
grandchildren from the 2 children who have 5 children each:\n   \\[\n   2 \
\\times 5 = 10\n   \\]\n\n3. Add the number of grandchildren from step 1 and \
