              StyleBox["\"Prompt:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"Uncle Jude baked 256 cookies. He gave 15 cookies to Tim, 23 \
cookies to Mike, kept some in the fridge and gave the rest to Anna. How many \
cookies did he put in the fridge if he gave twice as many cookies as he gave \
Tim to Anna?\""}, {
              StyleBox["\"Response:\"", Bold, StripOnInput -> False], 
              "\"To find out how many cookies Uncle Jude put in the fridge, \
we can follow these steps:\\n\\n1. Determine the total number of cookies \
given to Tim and Mike:\\n   \\\\[\\n   \\\\text{Cookies given to Tim} = 15\\n \
  \\\\]\\n   \\\\[\\n   \\\\text{Cookies given to Mike} = 23\\n   \\\\]\\n   \
\\\\[\\n   \\\\text{Total for Tim and Mike} = 15 + 23 = 38\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n2. \
Determine the number of cookies given to Anna:\\n   \\\\[\\n   \
\\\\text{Cookies given to Anna} = 2 \\\\times \\\\text{Cookies given to Tim} \
= 2 \\\\times 15 = 30\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n3. Calculate the total number of \
cookies given out:\\n   \\\\[\\n   \\\\text{Total cookies given out} = \
\\\\text{Cookies to Tim} + \\\\text{Cookies to Mike} + \\\\text{Cookies to \
Anna}\\n   \\\\]\\n   \\\\[\\n   = 15 + 23 + 30 = 68\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n4. \
Subtract the total number of cookies given out from the initial number of \
cookies to find how many were put in the fridge:\\n   \\\\[\\n   \
\\\\text{Cookies in the fridge} = \\\\text{Total cookies} - \\\\text{Total \
cookies given out}\\n   \\\\]\\n   \\\\[\\n   = 256 - 68 = 188\\n   \
\\\\]\\n\\nThus, Uncle Jude put 188 cookies in the fridge. \\n\\n**Final \
