the revenue from selling the books and the cost of making them. The profit \
equation can be set up as follows:\\n\\n   \\\\[\\n   \\\\text{Profit} = \
(\\\\text{Selling Price per Book} - \\\\text{Cost per Book}) \\\\times \
\\\\text{Number of Books Sold}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n   Given:\\n   - Selling Price \
per Book = $20\\n   - Cost per Book = $5\\n   - Profit = $120\\n\\n   \
Plugging in the values:\\n\\n   \\\\[\\n   120 = (20 - 5) \\\\times \
\\\\text{Number of Books Sold}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n   Simplifying:\\n\\n   \
\\\\[\\n   120 = 15 \\\\times \\\\text{Number of Books Sold}\\n   \\\\]\\n\\n \
